WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.119 --> 00:00:12.640
WIND BLOWS

2
00:00:14.359 --> 00:00:17.239
ENGINE RUMBLES

3
00:00:26.079 --> 00:00:27.719
FINN:
Sean. Billy. we're here.

4
00:00:40.799 --> 00:00:42.520
Can I shoot a rabbit?
- FINN LAUGHS

5
00:00:42.600 --> 00:00:43.560
Here.

6
00:00:44.079 --> 00:00:45.079
Go on.

7
00:00:45.159 --> 00:00:47.039
We'll meet you up
at the old barn. alright?

8
00:00:47.240 --> 00:00:48.079
SEAN:
Come on.

9
00:00:58.079 --> 00:00:59.159
It'll be OK.

10
00:01:22.039 --> 00:01:23.519
FINN:
Hold on there. boys.

11
00:01:30.079 --> 00:01:31.000
Come 'ere.

12
00:01:35.319 --> 00:01:37.640
We were born
into a certain world.

13
00:01:38.879 --> 00:01:40.280
It was chosen for us.

14
00:01:40.439 --> 00:01:41.359
Fated.

15
00:01:41.560 --> 00:01:43.599
Some might think it's brutal.

16
00:01:44.400 --> 00:01:45.799
I say it's glorious.

17
00:01:48.079 --> 00:01:49.560
Now. if you can do
this one thing

18
00:01:49.640 --> 00:01:51.719
you can have all
that it has to offer.

19
00:01:52.759 --> 00:01:53.920
Do you want that. son?

20
00:01:54.840 --> 00:01:55.759
Yeah.

21
00:02:16.840 --> 00:02:18.639
I want you to take
this man's life.

22
00:02:20.920 --> 00:02:22.000
What did he do?

23
00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:24.280
He made a bargain.

24
00:02:25.920 --> 00:02:27.319
Just like you're about to.

25
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:31.159
Once you enter this world.
you accept that you must kill

26
00:02:31.240 --> 00:02:33.039
or in turn you may be killed.

27
00:02:33.400 --> 00:02:35.920
Once you understand that rule.
it's easy.

28
00:02:37.360 --> 00:02:39.520
You can take a life
without hesitation.

29
00:02:40.840 --> 00:02:42.039
You can build an empire

30
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:43.879
be a king.

31
00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:06.120
Just breathe.

32
00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:23.960
Please. please...

33
00:03:24.479 --> 00:03:25.400
I'm sorry.

34
00:03:25.680 --> 00:03:27.400
I'm sorry. You don't have
to do this. please!

35
00:03:27.719 --> 00:03:29.360
Don't.
Please. I'm sorry.

36
00:03:30.039 --> 00:03:32.159
I'm sorry. please! Please...

37
00:03:32.639 --> 00:03:33.960
Please...
- Finn.

38
00:03:34.920 --> 00:03:36.360
MAN:
Please. I'm so sorry.

39
00:03:36.759 --> 00:03:37.639
No. no!

40
00:03:38.120 --> 00:03:39.680
No. please!

41
00:03:39.960 --> 00:03:41.840
No. don't. please! Please!

42
00:03:42.360 --> 00:03:43.400
Please!

43
00:03:43.479 --> 00:03:45.159
Just shoot the bucket.

44
00:03:46.039 --> 00:03:47.039
MAN:
Please!

45
00:03:47.439 --> 00:03:48.560
Please. no!

46
00:03:49.560 --> 00:03:50.719
MAN WAILS

47
00:03:51.240 --> 00:03:53.079
MAN SOBS

48
00:03:53.719 --> 00:03:55.400
Sorry! Christ. I'm sorry!

49
00:03:55.920 --> 00:03:57.840
Please. please!

50
00:03:58.599 --> 00:04:00.840
You don't have to do this!
I'm sorry!

51
00:04:01.360 --> 00:04:02.560
I'm sorry!

52
00:04:03.680 --> 00:04:04.599
Please!

53
00:04:04.919 --> 00:04:06.840
Oh. God... Christ!

54
00:04:06.919 --> 00:04:08.319
GUNSHOT

55
00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:19.879
COWS MOO

56
00:04:20.600 --> 00:04:22.959
ENGINE RUMBLES

57
00:04:25.920 --> 00:04:27.319
COWS MOO

58
00:04:34.480 --> 00:04:36.639
EXPLOSION
- COWS CRY

59
00:04:44.879 --> 00:04:46.199
COW GROANS

60
00:04:51.040 --> 00:04:52.240
MAN GRUNTS
- COW CRIES

61
00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:54.199
FLESH SQUELCHES

62
00:04:58.000 --> 00:04:59.720
IN KURDISH:

63
00:05:07.399 --> 00:05:08.680
SHE SPEAKS KURDISH

64
00:05:20.199 --> 00:05:21.279
MAN GRUNTS

65
00:05:28.040 --> 00:05:29.560
WOMAN YELLS IN KURDISH

66
00:05:31.759 --> 00:05:35.879
IN KURDISH:

67
00:05:39.639 --> 00:05:41.000
WOMAN YELLS

68
00:06:09.240 --> 00:06:12.319
MACHINERY WHIRS

69
00:06:14.360 --> 00:06:16.800
FLESH SLOPS

70
00:06:20.879 --> 00:06:23.040
The fuck is this?

71
00:06:30.720 --> 00:06:31.839
They're fucking empty!

72
00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:51.480
IN KURDISH:

73
00:07:03.040 --> 00:07:04.439
IN KURDISH:

74
00:07:16.079 --> 00:07:17.360
MEN CHATTER IN KURDISH

75
00:07:52.399 --> 00:07:53.840
DOORBELL RINGS

76
00:07:56.959 --> 00:07:57.920
Jack!

77
00:07:58.399 --> 00:08:00.079
Jack. open up!
- HE KNOCKS

78
00:08:02.120 --> 00:08:04.079
LOCK CLICKS
- DOOR OPENS

79
00:08:33.960 --> 00:08:35.000
HE YELLS

80
00:08:35.840 --> 00:08:37.919
ELLIOT BREATHES HEAVILY

81
00:08:38.159 --> 00:08:39.559
HE GRUNTS

82
00:08:44.399 --> 00:08:45.720
CHILD LAUGHS

83
00:08:58.679 --> 00:09:01.080
WOMAN: Psych evaluation.
D.I. Elliot Carter.

84
00:09:01.200 --> 00:09:05.080
In the presence of Dr May.
12th March. 2020.

85
00:09:06.519 --> 00:09:08.159
Have you had any trouble
sleeping?

86
00:09:09.639 --> 00:09:10.559
No.

87
00:09:13.200 --> 00:09:15.080
Any nightmares?
Negative thoughts?

88
00:09:16.879 --> 00:09:17.840
No.

89
00:09:20.840 --> 00:09:22.919
Experiencing a loss of appetite?

90
00:09:24.399 --> 00:09:25.320
<i>No.</i>

91
00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:27.919
He's been undercover
for two years.

92
00:09:28.480 --> 00:09:29.879
He's getting closer
to the violence

93
00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:31.799
but not to any evidence.

94
00:09:32.759 --> 00:09:34.440
This is how UCs get killed.

95
00:09:34.519 --> 00:09:36.320
DR MAY: <i>Feeling aggressive
towards others?</i>

96
00:09:37.200 --> 00:09:38.120
This is different.

97
00:09:38.200 --> 00:09:40.480
It's worse. He's unstable.

98
00:09:42.159 --> 00:09:44.000
DR MAY: <i>Do you think about
your wife Naomi?</i>

99
00:09:46.360 --> 00:09:48.039
How long has it been
since she died?

100
00:09:50.200 --> 00:09:51.320
HE SIGHS

101
00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:55.159
ELLIOT:
<i>Two years.</i>

102
00:09:56.399 --> 00:09:57.919
DR MAY:
<i>And your son. Samuel...</i>

103
00:09:58.679 --> 00:09:59.759
<i>or was it Sam?</i>

104
00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:05.960
<i>Samuel.</i>

105
00:10:07.120 --> 00:10:08.679
DR MAY:
<i>Do you think about Samuel?</i>

106
00:10:12.360 --> 00:10:13.639
<i>Of course I do.</i>

107
00:10:16.919 --> 00:10:18.240
Just let it play out.

108
00:10:18.360 --> 00:10:20.320
See what he comes up with.
That is all I'm asking.

109
00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:21.600
Is he compromised?

110
00:10:21.879 --> 00:10:24.039
Taken any risks we can't explain
to a judge?

111
00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:25.919
No.

112
00:10:29.080 --> 00:10:30.039
He's careful.

113
00:10:30.679 --> 00:10:32.039
We've been here before. Vic.

114
00:10:32.919 --> 00:10:36.240
Years of surveillance wasted
when a UC loses his way.

115
00:10:36.960 --> 00:10:38.440
Let's hope this is different.

116
00:10:46.440 --> 00:10:48.200
DOOR SHUTS
- SHE SIGHS

117
00:10:55.519 --> 00:10:57.639
VICKY:
You did it. He's keeping you in.

118
00:10:58.360 --> 00:10:59.639
We can do this. Vic.

119
00:11:00.440 --> 00:11:01.600
I've felt the shift.

120
00:11:02.679 --> 00:11:04.559
We know Sean threw a boy
off a building.

121
00:11:04.639 --> 00:11:06.600
And may he rest in peace
but if it doesn't connect

122
00:11:06.679 --> 00:11:09.200
to the shell companies.
or the asset funds

123
00:11:10.039 --> 00:11:11.799
it doesn't touch the Wallace
organisation.

124
00:11:12.080 --> 00:11:14.879
We know they launder through
their property empire. hmm?

125
00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:18.279
Sean is overseeing all that now.

126
00:11:18.360 --> 00:11:19.759
He's not just building
the towers.

127
00:11:19.840 --> 00:11:21.000
Then we'll need a paper trail.

128
00:11:22.679 --> 00:11:23.879
Alex?
- Dumani?

129
00:11:23.960 --> 00:11:25.240
He pushes the numbers.

130
00:11:25.519 --> 00:11:27.519
Keeps his nose clean.
Steers clear of the bodies.

131
00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:28.759
And that's helpful to us how?

132
00:11:28.840 --> 00:11:30.440
There's no way he can stay clean

133
00:11:30.519 --> 00:11:31.720
while Sean's running it.

134
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:33.960
And if we're lucky.
this will get messy.

135
00:11:34.080 --> 00:11:35.120
Lucky?

136
00:11:36.080 --> 00:11:37.600
For whom?
- PHONE BUZZES

137
00:11:41.639 --> 00:11:43.159
PHONE BUZZES

138
00:11:44.320 --> 00:11:45.320
PHONE BEEPS

139
00:11:48.240 --> 00:11:49.240
Yes. Mr Wallace.

140
00:12:07.799 --> 00:12:09.320
Fucking 'ell. Jack.

141
00:12:11.320 --> 00:12:12.799
FLIES BUZZ

142
00:12:15.240 --> 00:12:16.679
What does it look like to you?

143
00:12:17.519 --> 00:12:20.879
DISTANT DANCE MUSIC BLARES

144
00:12:25.080 --> 00:12:26.879
I mean. I dunno.

145
00:12:28.639 --> 00:12:31.519
A man doesn't fight for his life
then kill himself.

146
00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:35.240
You're the only one he told
about the Traveller kid.

147
00:12:37.159 --> 00:12:39.200
Lot of havoc being done
on your word.

148
00:13:16.399 --> 00:13:18.159
BABY CRIES

149
00:13:29.639 --> 00:13:30.840
NASIR:
...has done nothing

150
00:13:30.919 --> 00:13:32.759
to quell the rise
in foreign investors

151
00:13:32.840 --> 00:13:34.480
pushing up our property prices.

152
00:13:35.200 --> 00:13:41.799
IN URDU:

153
00:14:00.440 --> 00:14:01.320
HE SPEAKS URDU

154
00:14:04.039 --> 00:14:09.279
IN URDU:

155
00:14:14.679 --> 00:14:16.039
CROWD MUTTERS

156
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:27.080
CROWD MURMURS

157
00:14:31.159 --> 00:14:34.000
Should I become
the Mayor of London

158
00:14:34.960 --> 00:14:38.159
I am committed to ending
this cycle of addiction

159
00:14:38.240 --> 00:14:39.679
and violence on the streets.

160
00:14:39.919 --> 00:14:42.879
I will be demanding more police.
more care

161
00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:44.039
in our communities...

162
00:14:44.120 --> 00:14:49.320
IN URDU:

163
00:14:49.519 --> 00:14:52.519
And I want people to stop
looking at them

164
00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:54.679
as potential extremists
and to start

165
00:14:54.759 --> 00:14:56.960
seeing them as leaders of men.

166
00:14:57.279 --> 00:14:58.799
CROWD MURMURS

167
00:15:10.480 --> 00:15:12.279
IN URDU:

168
00:15:59.720 --> 00:16:02.360
SEAN: They got to Jack.
Slit his wrists.

169
00:16:02.879 --> 00:16:04.039
ALEX:
Fuck.

170
00:16:05.879 --> 00:16:08.120
Whoever killed Finn.
they're tidying up.

171
00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:10.480
SEAN:
That's what it looks like.

172
00:16:11.440 --> 00:16:12.879
So what do we know
about the car?

173
00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:16.039
The number plates belong
to Patrick Day.

174
00:16:16.519 --> 00:16:18.000
Who?
- One of Kinney's crew.

175
00:16:18.159 --> 00:16:19.159
Where is he now?

176
00:16:19.279 --> 00:16:21.799
Gone. Car dumped outside
a warehouse. south.

177
00:16:22.200 --> 00:16:23.200
Three bodies inside.

178
00:16:26.679 --> 00:16:27.919
We're on the Kinney thing.
right?

179
00:16:28.039 --> 00:16:30.360
We've got uniform shaking down
sites now.

180
00:16:32.159 --> 00:16:33.399
Always a step ahead.

181
00:16:36.240 --> 00:16:37.639
ALEX:
How you holding up?

182
00:16:39.840 --> 00:16:41.320
What's Asif doing here?

183
00:16:43.120 --> 00:16:44.960
Listen. As your partner.
I made a call.

184
00:16:45.639 --> 00:16:47.039
We let Asif trade.

185
00:16:48.799 --> 00:16:49.960
We need him.

186
00:16:51.600 --> 00:16:52.840
My cows.

187
00:16:53.159 --> 00:16:54.440
Thirty years...

188
00:16:55.120 --> 00:16:56.320
we've never had a problem.

189
00:16:56.480 --> 00:16:59.759
Thirty years and you
didn't even come to the funeral.

190
00:16:59.879 --> 00:17:01.120
I sent my son.

191
00:17:02.759 --> 00:17:03.879
My flesh and blood.

192
00:17:04.519 --> 00:17:07.160
Asif. you know your business
is important to us.

193
00:17:08.559 --> 00:17:09.880
We are in...

194
00:17:10.599 --> 00:17:12.000
an adjustment period.

195
00:17:13.519 --> 00:17:15.359
DOOR SHUTS
- Sean is running things now.

196
00:17:16.519 --> 00:17:17.839
It's what Finn wanted.

197
00:17:23.359 --> 00:17:24.359
DOOR OPENS

198
00:17:29.359 --> 00:17:31.519
ASIF: My deepest condolences
for your loss.

199
00:17:32.319 --> 00:17:35.559
Finn was a great man.
an excellent business partner.

200
00:17:36.240 --> 00:17:37.559
We know who the shooter was.

201
00:17:38.279 --> 00:17:40.160
A Traveller kid.
My men are looking.

202
00:17:40.400 --> 00:17:41.799
You've got trouble
with these people?

203
00:17:41.880 --> 00:17:43.400
Nothing to warrant killing him.

204
00:17:45.039 --> 00:17:46.160
That's not good.

205
00:17:46.720 --> 00:17:47.960
A man of Finn's standing

206
00:17:48.039 --> 00:17:49.960
should not be that easy
to take out.

207
00:17:50.680 --> 00:17:52.240
Your organisation is weak
somewhere.

208
00:17:53.599 --> 00:17:54.559
What are you saying?

209
00:17:54.640 --> 00:17:55.799
First they come for you

210
00:17:56.039 --> 00:17:58.799
now someone has got to
your business partner. Me.

211
00:18:00.519 --> 00:18:02.400
My shipment was hit yesterday.

212
00:18:02.519 --> 00:18:04.200
I gave an order that no one
moves any dope

213
00:18:04.279 --> 00:18:05.599
until I find the killer.

214
00:18:05.839 --> 00:18:07.079
It obviously didn't reach you.

215
00:18:07.279 --> 00:18:09.960
If you impose an embargo.
you will start a war.

216
00:18:10.079 --> 00:18:13.720
A war was started
when my father was shot.

217
00:18:15.279 --> 00:18:17.240
ASIF SCOFFS

218
00:18:19.640 --> 00:18:21.599
You've got his temper.

219
00:18:22.839 --> 00:18:25.240
Believe me. if they were to
kill my son...

220
00:18:26.640 --> 00:18:29.200
I would wipe out
their bloodline.

221
00:18:30.880 --> 00:18:33.359
But I would not lose a Rupee
in the act.

222
00:18:37.000 --> 00:18:38.279
Be smart. Sean.

223
00:18:41.359 --> 00:18:43.519
Anyone not helping find
Dad's killer

224
00:18:44.519 --> 00:18:46.079
looks suspect to me.

225
00:18:47.079 --> 00:18:49.039
He always said you wanted
a piece of London.

226
00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:51.720
Now your son's running
for mayor.

227
00:18:53.039 --> 00:18:56.559
Without our support.
it might be difficult for Nasir.

228
00:19:04.400 --> 00:19:05.480
Sean...

229
00:19:08.400 --> 00:19:11.200
I'm down five million pounds.

230
00:19:12.920 --> 00:19:14.119
What is bad for me...

231
00:19:15.119 --> 00:19:16.440
is bad for you.

232
00:19:23.839 --> 00:19:26.119
MUSIC: “Tears On My Pillow” by
Little Anthony & The Imperials

233
00:19:26.200 --> 00:19:28.039
MARIAN:
This is shaming us as a family.

234
00:19:28.519 --> 00:19:30.359
There was a time when nobody
would've dared

235
00:19:30.440 --> 00:19:31.559
touch Finn Wallace.

236
00:19:31.920 --> 00:19:33.000
SEAN:
They got lucky.

237
00:19:34.559 --> 00:19:36.240
Why was he even in that flat?

238
00:19:38.920 --> 00:19:40.640
We have to be honest
with ourselves.

239
00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:45.319
What if it was personal?

240
00:19:46.359 --> 00:19:47.680
Some woman's husband.

241
00:19:47.880 --> 00:19:50.200
We're not picking the flesh
off a dead man's bones.

242
00:19:50.519 --> 00:19:51.559
We have to.

243
00:19:53.319 --> 00:19:55.960
<i># I wouldn't hesitate #</i>

244
00:19:57.839 --> 00:19:59.200
How did it go with Asif?

245
00:20:00.599 --> 00:20:01.799
He's taken a hit.

246
00:20:02.119 --> 00:20:04.240
A missing shipment isn't good
for any of us.

247
00:20:04.920 --> 00:20:06.759
If there's anyone dealing smack
in London

248
00:20:06.880 --> 00:20:08.079
I want to know about it.

249
00:20:11.039 --> 00:20:12.039
What can I do?

250
00:20:13.200 --> 00:20:14.240
Nothing.

251
00:20:21.359 --> 00:20:24.519
<i># Love is not a toy #</i>

252
00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:28.000
<i># When you find the one
you love #</i>

253
00:20:28.160 --> 00:20:30.599
<i># She'll fill your heart
with joy... #</i>

254
00:20:30.720 --> 00:20:32.200
I'm gonna make
things right. Mum.

255
00:20:32.599 --> 00:20:34.880
<i># If we could start anew... #</i>

256
00:20:35.000 --> 00:20:36.160
I know you will.

257
00:20:36.400 --> 00:20:38.640
<i># I wouldn't hesitate #</i>

258
00:20:39.880 --> 00:20:41.799
I'm proud of you both.

259
00:20:43.240 --> 00:20:47.200
Billy's clean.
and you're strong.

260
00:20:49.359 --> 00:20:51.759
<i># Pain in my heart #</i>

261
00:20:51.880 --> 00:20:54.400
If it was a woman.
she didn't love my husband.

262
00:20:56.640 --> 00:20:57.880
If she had...

263
00:20:58.680 --> 00:21:01.039
she wouldn't have
had him shot in the face.

264
00:21:02.119 --> 00:21:03.319
<i># Oh. oh #</i>

265
00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:05.960
<i># You... #</i>
- MUSIC FADES

266
00:21:10.920 --> 00:21:12.079
DOOR OPENS

267
00:21:17.079 --> 00:21:20.119
